What are ceramic susceptors in semiconductor equipment?Ceramic susceptors are components used in semiconductor manufacturing equipment to uniformly absorb and distribute heat during processes like epitaxial growth. They are typically made from materials such as graphite coated with silicon carbide (SiC), pure silicon carbide, or silicon. marketresearchintellect.com
